        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Preventing Crimes Against Veterans Act of 2016</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to declare that any person who knowingly engages in any scheme or artifice to defraud an individual of veterans' benefits, or in connection with obtaining veteran's benefits for that individual, shall be fined, imprisoned not more than five years, or both.</p>]]></text>
